:R-HSA-199992  a            obo:GO_0006892 , owl:NamedIndividual ;
        rdfs:comment        "After passing through the Golgi complex, secretory cargo is packaged into post-Golgi transport intermediates (post-Golgi), which translocate plus-end directed along microtubules to the plasma membrane. There at least two classes of clathrin coated vesicles in cells, one predominantly Golgi-associated, involved in budding from the trans-Golgi network and the other at the plasma membrane. Here the clathrin-coated vesicles emerging from the Golgi apparatus are triggered by the heterotetrameric adaptor protein complex, AP-1 at the trans-Golgi network membrane. The cargo can be transmembrane, membrane associated or golgi luminal proteins. Each step in the vesicle sculpting pathway, gathers cargo and clathrin triskeletons, until a complete vesicular sphere is formed. With the scission of the membrane the vesicle is released and eventually losses its clathrin coat." ;
        rdfs:label          "trans-Golgi Network Vesicle Budding" ;
        dc:contributor      "GOC:reactome_curators" , "Reviewed: Rush, MG, 2008-01-11 00:00:00" , "Reviewed: Simpson, Jeremy C, 2009-08-27" , "Edited: Gillespie, ME, 2008-05-21 20:31:41" , "Authored: Gillespie, ME, 2008-05-21 20:31:41" ;
        dc:date             "2026-06-29" ;
        pav:providedBy      "https://reactome.org" ;
        oboInOwl:hasDbXref  "R-HSA-199992" ;
        skos:narrower       <http://model.geneontology.org/R-HSA-199991/R-HSA-199991> ;
        skos:note           "org.biopax.paxtools.model.level3.Pathway" .

